6 EXACT(<text_1>, <text_2>) Checks if two strings are identical (EXACT() is case sensitive).
6 FIND(<text_tofind>, <in_text>) Returns the starting position a text within another text 
(FIND() is case sensitive)F
6 FORMAT(<value>, <format>) Converts a value to a text in the specified number formatF
6 LEFT(<text>, <num_chars>) Returns the number of characters from the start of a string.
6 RIGHT(<text>, <num_chars>) Returns the number of characters from the end of a stringF
6 LEN(<text>) Returns the number of characters in a string of textF
6 LOWER(<text>) Converts all letters in a string to lowercaseF
6 UPPER(<text>) Converts all letters in a string to uppercaseF
6 TRIM(<text>) Remove all spaces from a text stringF
6 CONCATENATE(<text_1>, <text_2>) Joins two strings together into one stringF
6 SUBSTITUTE(<text>, <old_text>, <new_text>, <instance_num>) Replaces existing text with new text in a stringF
6 REPLACE(<old_text>, <start_posotion>, <num_chars>, <new_text>) Replaces part of a string with 
a new string.
